VALUES
(44, 2, 17, 26, 11, 19, 19, 'I will pour out of my Spirit', 'Connection of Spirit and Transformation', 'This connection highlights the theme of God giving His Spirit to transform hearts. Both passages emphasize the impartation of a new spirit and the resulting prophetic activity or heart change.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 18, 48, 3, 28, 28, 'my servants and on my handmaidens', 'Unity in the Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the inclusivity of God''s Spirit. Acts 2:18 speaks of all servants prophesying, while Galatians 3:28 declares unity among all believers, regardless of status or gender.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 18, 51, 3, 11, 11, 'my Spirit; and they shall prophesy', 'Unity in the Spirit', 'This connection highlights the inclusivity of the Spirit''s outpouring and the unity in Christ. Both passages emphasize that all people, regardless of background or status, are empowered and valued in the community of believers.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 18, 46, 7, 21, 22, 'my servants and on my handmaidens', 'Servanthood and Spiritual Freedom', 'Both passages emphasize the role of servants in God''s plan. Acts highlights the outpouring of the Spirit on servants, while 1 Corinthians discusses their status as free in Christ. This connection highlights the transformative nature of servanthood in the spiritual realm.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 18, 44, 21, 10, 10, 'they shall prophesy', 'Connection of Prophecy in Acts', 'This connection highlights the theme of prophecy, as both passages reference individuals who prophesy. Acts 2:18 mentions that God''s Spirit will enable servants to prophesy, while Acts 21:10 introduces Agabus, a prophet from Judea.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 19, 29, 2, 30, 31, 'wonders in heaven above, and signs in the earth beneath', 'Connection of Signs and Wonders', 'Both passages emphasize ''wonders in heaven'' and ''blood, and fire, and smoke.'' This connection highlights the prophetic nature of the signs preceding the ''great and terrible day of the Lord.''', 'prophecy', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 19, 36, 1, 14, 18, 'wonders in heaven above', 'Day of the Lord''s Wrath', 'Both passages emphasize the impending ''day of the Lord'' characterized by signs and wonders, as well as distress and destruction. Acts 2:19''s ''wonders in heaven'' and Zephaniah''s ''day of wrath'' depict a time of divine judgment and upheaval.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 19, 39, 4, 1, 6, 'signs in the earth beneath', 'Judgment and Signs Connection', 'Both passages emphasize impending judgment and signs. Acts 2:19 mentions ''wonders'' and ''signs,'' while Malachi 4:1 speaks of a ''day'' that will burn the wicked. This connection highlights the theme of divine intervention and the consequences for the unrighteous.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 20, 61, 3, 10, 10, 'that great and notable day of the Lord', 'Day of the Lord Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the dramatic events associated with the ''day of the Lord.'' Acts 2:20 describes celestial signs preceding this day, while 2 Peter 3:10 depicts the heavens and earth undergoing significant transformation.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 20, 30, 8, 9, 9, 'the sun shall be turned into darkness', 'Connection of Darkness and Prophecy', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of darkness occurring as a sign of impending divine judgment. The imagery of the sun being darkened in both verses serves to highlight the seriousness of the ''day of the Lord.''', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 20, 40, 24, 29, 29, 'the sun shall be turned into darkness', 'Cosmic Signs Before the Day', 'Both passages emphasize cosmic disturbances, specifically the darkening of the sun and the moon''s altered state, occurring before significant events. This connection highlights a prophetic theme regarding signs preceding the ''great and notable day of the Lord'' and the tribulation.', 'prophecy', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 20, 39, 4, 5, 5, 'great and notable day of the Lord', 'Connection of the Day of the Lord', 'Both passages emphasize the ''great day of the Lord,'' highlighting a significant eschatological event. The imagery of darkness and blood in Acts parallels the prophetic warning in Malachi about the coming of Elijah before this day.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 20, 52, 5, 2, 2, 'that great and notable day of the Lord', 'Day of the Lord Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the ''day of the Lord,'' indicating a significant and imminent event. Acts 2:20 describes cosmic signs preceding this day, while 1 Thessalonians 5:2 highlights its unexpected arrival.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 20, 29, 2, 1, 1, NULL, 'Connection of the Day of the Lord', 'Both passages emphasize the imminent arrival of the ''day of the Lord.'' Acts 2:20 references cosmic signs that precede this significant day, while Joel 2:1 calls for alarm as it approaches.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 20, 29, 3, 14, 14, NULL, 'Connection of the Day of the Lord', 'Both passages emphasize the imminent arrival of the ''day of the Lord.'' Acts 2:20 speaks of cosmic signs preceding this day, while Joel 3:14 highlights the urgency of decision-making as this day approaches.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 21, 45, 10, 12, 13, NULL, 'Salvation through Calling on the Lord', 'Both passages emphasize that calling on the name of the Lord leads to salvation. They highlight the inclusivity of this promise, applying to both Jews and Greeks.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 21, 29, 2, 32, 32, 'whosoever shall call on the name of the Lord', 'Connection of Salvation and Deliverance', 'Both passages emphasize calling on the name of the Lord for salvation or deliverance. This connection highlights the universal invitation for whosoever seeks the Lord''s help.', 'theme', 0.51, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 21, 19, 86, 5, 5, NULL, 'Calling on the Lord', 'Both passages emphasize the act of calling upon the Lord for salvation and mercy. They highlight the accessibility of God''s goodness and forgiveness to those who seek Him.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 21, 44, 22, 16, 16, NULL, 'Calling on the Lord', 'Both passages emphasize the act of calling on the name of the Lord as essential for salvation and the washing away of sins. This connection highlights the importance of invoking the Lord''s name in the process of salvation.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 21, 58, 4, 16, 16, 'call on the name of the Lord', 'Connection of Salvation and Grace', 'Both passages emphasize the act of calling upon the Lord for salvation and the approach to His grace. Acts 2:21 highlights the necessity of calling on the Lord, while Hebrews 4:16 invites believers to come boldly to obtain mercy and grace.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 21, 46, 1, 2, 2, NULL, 'Calling on the Lord', 'Both passages emphasize the act of calling upon the name of the Lord for salvation. Acts 2:21 states that whosoever calls on the name of the Lord shall be saved, while 1 Corinthians 1:2 mentions those who call upon the name of Jesus Christ. This connection highlights the importance of invoking the name of the Lord in the context of salvation.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 21, 40, 28, 19, 19, 'call on the name of the Lord', 'Salvation and Baptism Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation through calling on the Lord and the directive to baptize in His name. Both passages emphasize the importance of invoking the name of the Lord for salvation and the act of baptism as a public declaration of faith.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 22, 43, 3, 2, 2, 'miracles and wonders and signs', 'Connection of Miracles and Approval', 'Both passages emphasize the miracles performed by Jesus as evidence of his divine approval. Acts 2:22 states he was ''approved of God'' through miracles, while John 3:2 acknowledges that no one can perform such miracles ''except God be with him.''', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 22, 40, 12, 28, 28, 'miracles and wonders and signs', 'Connection of Miracles and Authority', 'Both passages emphasize the role of divine power in Jesus'' ministry. Acts 2:22 mentions ''miracles and wonders and signs'' as evidence of Jesus'' approval by God, while Matthew 12:28 refers to casting out devils by ''the Spirit of God'' as a sign of the kingdom''s arrival.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 22, 42, 11, 20, 20, 'approved of God among you by miracles', 'Divine Approval and Power', 'Both passages emphasize the divine approval of Jesus through miraculous acts. Acts 2:22 highlights Jesus as ''approved of God'' by miracles, while Luke 11:20 refers to casting out devils by ''the finger of God,'' indicating divine authority.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 22, 43, 14, 10, 11, 'miracles and wonders and signs', 'Connection of Divine Works', 'Both passages emphasize that the works performed are by divine authority. Acts highlights Jesus as a man approved by God through miracles, while John asserts that the Father does the works through Him.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 22, 44, 4, 10, 10, 'Jesus of Nazareth', 'Connection of Jesus'' Authority', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus of Nazareth as a man approved by God through miracles. They also highlight the significance of His resurrection and authority in healing.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 22, 40, 9, 8, 8, 'approved of God among you by miracles', 'Divine Power and Approval', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine approval and power. Acts 2:22 speaks of Jesus being approved by God through miracles, while Matthew 9:8 notes that the multitudes glorified God for giving power to men, suggesting a shared recognition of divine authority.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 22, 58, 2, 4, 4, 'miracles and wonders and signs', 'Connection of Signs and Wonders', 'Both passages emphasize the role of signs and wonders in validating God''s message. Acts 2:22 highlights Jesus'' miracles, while Hebrews 2:4 mentions God bearing witness through signs and wonders.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 2, 23, 42, 22, 22, 22, 'determinate counsel', 'Divine Determination in Betrayal', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of divine determination in the events leading to Jesus'' crucifixion. Acts 2:23 mentions ''determinate counsel'' while Luke 22:22 states ''as it was determined,'' linking the foreknowledge of God to the betrayal and crucifixion.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
